-- West Brom Beats Sunderland 4-2, Moves to Third in Premier League
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-11-24T14:59:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-24/west-brom-beats-sunderland-4-2-moves-to-third-in-premier-league.html
West Bromwich Albion beat Sunderland
4-2 to move above Chelsea into third place in English soccer’s
Premier League.  Zoltan Gera, Shane Long, Romelu Lukaku and Marc-Antoine
Fortune scored the goals at Sunderland’s Stadium of Light as
West Brom won its fourth straight match. The Baggies have 26
points, two more than Chelsea, and are just two points behind
first-place Manchester City.  Craig Gardener and Stephane Sessegnon scored for
Sunderland, which lost for the third time in four league games.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  